<br>
The set up: catch the boat from Freeport East and you will enter the Ocean of Tears(OOT). Get off on the first dock you reach. This is the Sisters of Erollisi Island, or Sister Island for short. I bind myself here since this is the vendor merchant NPC that I con Ally to. Now, head straight west. You will pass by one island before you reach the second island. The first island contains the spawn for the Ancient cyclops(Jboots quest MOB) as well as a vendor. The second island you see is the Seafury island. You will see many one-eyed huge giants roaming it.<br>
<br>
Now, there are two situations for hunting on the island. If you have the Gornit camp or if you do not. Gornit is a giant that spawns on the south-west corner of the seafury island. He drops upwards of 40pp sometimes and averages out at about 30pp per kill. He spawns every 6-7 minutes.<br>
<br>
If you DO NOT have Gornit:<br>
To set up, summon a level 49 Water pet. Cast BOIII and your DS on him then pull a seafury to the water's edge with Burst of Flame. Go ahead and sic the pet on him then sit down and START FISHING! Yes, that's right, start fishing. Don't heal the pet. He should be able to solo at most 3 seafuries(usually he can do 2 before running out of health or the DS dropping). Just keep repeating the pull until the pet is at about 20 health. Chain cast a new pet before your living pet dies and continue fishing. Toss a nuke in every now and again if you have lots of mana or KEI.<br>
<br>
Essentially all you are doing is pulling for your pet and medding up. Your only mana costs should be the chain casting of pets, BOIII on each pet and the DS for each pet.  The seafuries sometimes drop gems or jewelry that sells for 50pp+. Keep everything(except the toes and research components, most are worth 1pp at most) to sell to the vendors. If you are KOS to the sisters, there is a high elf vendor on the Ancient Cyclops island.<br>
<br>
IF YOU HAVE GORNIT:<br>
If you do get his camp then everything will be the same as above with one exception: you can kill Gornit.  <br>
<br>
Do exactly this: get your pet. BOIII on pet, DS, kill Gornit. Loot Gornit. Now you have enough time to pull and kill TWO seafuries before Gornit pops again. If you pet is around 20% hp and Gornit pops, just send him to attack. Chain summon a new one before it dies and you're all set to repeat the cycle.<br>
<br>
<br>
Just keep fishing while your pet fights for you. This ensures that you are constantly medding up. Don't worry about summoning items for your pet(ie. armor, weapons, etc.) because you will be burning through pets. At level 51 it took me about 17 malachite of summoning MSII to get a little over one yellow and one blue exp. So it doesn't take that much malachite but I still bring a ton.<br>
<br>
I arrived at the island at level 49. I am now two yellows into 51 and have made over 4k pp while I have been here and my fishing skill went from 0 to 98. I'm staying until I hit 52 or 53 depending on the speed of exp after 52. Good luck!<br>
<br>
The process becomes easier with the level 50 MSII pet. It is better than the 49 water AND you can cannibalize it for mana if you're OOM. Oh yeah, stay away from Quag Malestrom and the tainted/corrupted cyclops. They aren't worth fighting and will most likely drop you if you aren't careful. That about covers it! <p>-Saynac</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utangting.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TangTing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#333333>(10/10/02 1:31:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:</span><hr size=1> I will have to give this a try when and if I hit 49.  Gornit's going to be hard to get - constantly camped on my server, but I have a score to settle with those SeaFury's.  I swam to the wrong island in OOT once and WHAM!   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utangting.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TangTing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#333333>(10/11/02 12:12:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Seafuries</span><hr size=1> Got up early, Gornit camped.  The mana/xp ratio at 46 isn't great, but they moved the xp bar a bit.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usaynac.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saynac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: